<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-05T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-05T18:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/6.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-05T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 5, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>This Government trusts that the President of Cuba pursuant to his
                            declarations reported by you in your No. 585 of January 9, 1913, will
                            take action to restrict the amnesty to political offenders.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>